executedeno.description:
**TYPESCRIPT EXECUTION ENGINE** - Execute TypeScript/JavaScript with Deno runtime. **ALWAYS USE FOR TYPE-SAFE OPERATIONS** and when TypeScript validation is needed.

**MANDATORY WORKING DIRECTORY:**
• workingDirectory parameter is **REQUIRED** and **MUST BE SET** - specify the exact directory context
• Each execution runs in the specified directory as its current working directory
• Deno resolves imports and modules relative to the working directory
• File permissions and access are scoped to the working directory context
• **ALWAYS provide this parameter** - execution will fail without it

**AUTOMATIC RESPONSE TRUNCATION & OVERFLOW HANDLING:**
• **25k Token Limit**: Responses exceeding ~25,000 tokens are automatically truncated
• **Overflow Storage**: Excess content stored in `.call_overflow/` directory within workingDirectory
• **Seamless Retrieval**: Use `retrieve_overflow` tool to access stored content chunks
• **Preservation Guarantee**: Leading content always preserved, nothing lost permanently
• **Clear Instructions**: Truncation notices provide exact steps to retrieve remaining content
• **Example**: If truncated, response shows "Use 'retrieve_overflow' tool with file: 'overflow_executedeno_1234567890.json'"

**COMPREHENSIVE BATCHING CAPABILITIES:**
This tool can batch ALL of the following TypeScript/JavaScript operations:
• **Type Checking**: Validate multiple TypeScript files and interfaces simultaneously
• **Module Testing**: Import and test multiple TypeScript modules together
• **API Integration**: Batch HTTP requests with full type safety and error handling
• **File Processing**: Read, analyze, and transform multiple files with type validation
• **Code Generation**: Generate TypeScript types, interfaces, and implementation files
• **Schema Validation**: Validate multiple data structures against TypeScript interfaces
• **Web Standards Testing**: Test Web APIs, fetch requests, and browser compatibility
• **Performance Benchmarking**: Type-safe performance testing of multiple algorithms
• **Configuration Parsing**: Validate and process multiple config files with types
• **Security Analysis**: Type-safe validation of security patterns and implementations

**ADVANCED BATCHING STRATEGIES:**
```typescript
// EXCELLENT: Complete TypeScript workflow
interface APIEndpoint { url: string; method: string; expectedStatus: number; }
interface FileAnalysis { path: string; valid: boolean; issues: string[]; }

// Batch API testing + file validation + type checking
const endpoints: APIEndpoint[] = [
  { url: 'https://api1.com/health', method: 'GET', expectedStatus: 200 },
  { url: 'https://api2.com/status', method: 'GET', expectedStatus: 200 }
];

const configFiles = ['config.ts', 'types.ts', 'utils.ts'];

const results = {
  apiTests: await Promise.allSettled(
    endpoints.map(async (endpoint): Promise<{ endpoint: APIEndpoint; success: boolean }> => {
      const response = await fetch(endpoint.url, { method: endpoint.method });
      return { endpoint, success: response.status === endpoint.expectedStatus };
    })
  ),
  fileAnalysis: configFiles.map((file): FileAnalysis => {
    try {
      const content = Deno.readTextFileSync(file);
      const issues: string[] = [];
      if (!content.includes('export')) issues.push('No exports found');
      if (content.includes('any')) issues.push('Uses any type');
      return { path: file, valid: issues.length === 0, issues };
    } catch (error) {
      return { path: file, valid: false, issues: [error.message] };
    }
  }),
  typeValidation: validateComplexTypes()
};

console.log('TypeScript Analysis:', Deno.inspect(results, { depth: 3 }));
```

**REPLACE ALL TYPESCRIPT TOOLS:**
• Instead of tsc → use Deno's built-in TypeScript compilation with batch processing
• Instead of separate test runners → use Deno.test() in comprehensive batched scenarios
• Instead of external formatters → use Deno fmt programmatically on multiple files
• Instead of multiple HTTP clients → use native fetch with full type safety
• Instead of separate linters → use Deno lint with custom validation logic
• Instead of webpack/bundlers → use Deno bundle with dependency analysis

**TYPE-DRIVEN DEVELOPMENT PATTERNS:**
• **Interface-First Design**: Define comprehensive interfaces for all batch operations
• **Generic Batch Processing**: Create reusable typed functions for common patterns
• **Union Type Handling**: Use discriminated unions for multiple operation types
• **Type Guard Implementation**: Runtime validation with compile-time type safety
• **Mapped Type Utilities**: Transform types programmatically for batch operations

**WEB API & SECURITY OPTIMIZATION:**
• **Batch HTTP Operations**: Promise.allSettled() with full type safety and error handling
• **Stream Processing**: Use Web Streams API for efficient large data processing
• **Caching Strategies**: Leverage Deno's built-in caching with type validation
• **Permission Management**: Runs with --allow-all for comprehensive operations
• **Security Validation**: Type-safe input validation and output sanitization

**WORKING DIRECTORY FUNCTIONALITY:**
• **Import Resolution**: TypeScript/JavaScript imports resolved relative to workingDirectory
• **Type Definition Access**: .d.ts files and @types packages accessed from working directory
• **File Operations**: All Deno file APIs operate within working directory context
• **Module Cache**: Deno module cache scoped to working directory dependencies
• **Configuration Files**: deno.json, import_map.json loaded from working directory

**OUTPUT OPTIMIZATION FOR DENO:**
• Use Deno.inspect() for superior object formatting with type information
• Leverage built-in formatters and type-aware validators
• Implement streaming for large data processing with type safety
• Use structured logging with typed log entries
• Return typed results with comprehensive error information

**PERFORMANCE & EFFICIENCY:**
• **Parallel Type Checking**: Validate multiple files simultaneously
• **Concurrent API Testing**: Batch HTTP requests with proper error boundaries
• **Memory Efficiency**: Use generators and iterators for large dataset processing
• **Compilation Caching**: Leverage Deno's built-in compilation cache
• **Dependency Optimization**: Analyze and optimize import graphs
